reviews.name: Wilson Medical Center Neodesha

reviews_data.review_text:
My son had speech therapy at WMC rehab and all the staff there was absolutely amazing and SO kind!
I was shocked that my son received mail from them wishing him a good school year and that they will miss him. Shows how much they truly care! ❤️
One of the best experiences I've had in an emergency room with a hook buried in my thumb. No pain,very quick. I felt very comfortable and reassured by nurse and doctor. Very Good place and people.

My very ill daughter was treated horrible by the nurse & the ER doctor.  They had absolutely no empathy for her as she was very sick and landed in MAdonna Rehab for recovery.   I would never take someone I loved to this ER.  The nurse was beyond rude and unprofessional. The Dr was just an overall jerk!   They cared less about my little girl.
It's always clean, the staff is friendly and helpful.
What a bunch of cruel, apathetic, immoral, bunch of Quacks. Refusing medical treatment in an emergency is against the law.

I go there every month to visit my doctor. When have to get labs done or xrays or a scan, they are the best at doing them. They treat you like a person and they go out of their way to make your experience their more  enjoyable and not so inperisible.

I went into the ER and I was having panic attacks and a bleeding face. The Nurses and the Dr were very professional and calming despite my best efforts. I have a bad phobia of needles and shots; I needed stitches and a tetanus shot. The Dr was quick and soothing when giving me stitches, And I didn't even notice when the Nurse gave me my booster. Seriously can't recommend this ER enough.

I needed to go to ER. They answered & saw me right away. This hospital has much to offer in many circumstances. It is a very clean hospital with very caring & knowledgeable staff & the best doctors. Quality of care is very important & I have absolutely no complaints.

I had outpatient surgery in late October and will have another procedure next week at this facility.  Obviously returning to the same medical center shows the faith I have in them and the staff displayed professionalism as well as a sincere concern for me as a patient.
Very professional employees.......couldn't ask for  nicer or more friendly folks! Nice Hospital atmosphere
Just sat in the waiting area of the emergency room for almost a hour and did not get any help. I will not be going back to this hospital.
No waiting like the Independence ER.
Good place to go when  sick or need medical  care
Great people Becky is the best ever!!!!
liked it very much
They are generally very helpful
Very rude unprofessional overnight staff!!!!!
Satisfied with service.
Rude
Badnice
